# Project Rules

## Product Summary
- jarizz is a small, native macOS menubar app that provides one unified UI for talking to many AI backends.
- The app runs as a menubar icon only (no Dock icon).
- A user-configurable global hotkey shows and hides the main UI (popover or compact floating panel).
- Long-term backends:
  - Local CLI agents: claude, copilot, codex, gemini CLI (whatever is installed on the machine).
  - Web AI services: embedded in-app browser (for example https://gemini.google.com/app) with full login and session support.

## Project Shape
- This project is configured for SwarmForge with four Claude-backed agents: specifier, coder, refactorer, and architect.
- Project language: Swift.
- UI framework: SwiftUI.
- Platform: macOS only.
- Minimum macOS version: 14.0.

## Technology Stack
- Web embedding (future slices): WKWebView via WebKit, not an external browser tab.
- Build layout: Swift Package Manager for testable libraries plus an Xcode app target for the .app bundle.
- Dependencies: prefer Apple frameworks; avoid Electron and other heavy third-party UI stacks.
- Bundle identifier placeholder: com.jarizz.app.
- Menubar icon: SF Symbol bubble.left.and.bubble.right until a custom asset exists.
- Default global hotkey: Control+Option+Space (configurable; persistence is a later slice).

## Architecture Principles
- Maximize testable JarizzCore modules; keep AppKit, SwiftUI, and WebKit at thin adapter edges.
- Future provider model (document now, implement in later slices):
  - AIProvider protocol with two kinds:
    - LocalCLIProvider: spawns and streams a local binary found on PATH.
    - WebServiceProvider: loads a configured URL in WKWebView, preserving cookies and authentication state.
- Configuration persistence (future): ~/Library/Application Support/jarizz/ as JSON or plist.
- Global hotkey monitoring will eventually need Accessibility approval; degrade gracefully so menubar click still toggles the popover when hotkey permission is denied.

## MVP Scope — Slice 1: App Shell

In scope:
- App launches and shows a menubar status item (jarizz icon or placeholder SF Symbol).
- Global hotkey toggles visibility of a popover or panel anchored to the menubar item.
- Popover contains a placeholder empty state (for example a jarizz title with no provider UI yet).
- Hotkey is configurable in code via constants for now; persistence is a later slice.
- Clicking the menubar icon also toggles the popover.
- Popover dismisses on outside click or Escape.
- App is agent-accessible: LSUIElement menubar-only, no Dock icon.
- Unit tests cover pure logic in JarizzCore (hotkey parsing, toggle state), not live GUI rendering.

Out of scope for slice 1:
- Provider configuration UI.
- Spawning local CLI agents.
- WKWebView, web AI services, and authentication flows.
- Chat history, streaming responses, and multi-tab providers.
- Settings window beyond a hardcoded default hotkey constant.

## Roadmap Phases
1. Shell — menubar, hotkey, empty popover (current slice).
2. Settings — persist hotkey and basic app preferences.
3. Provider registry — add, edit, and remove configured providers (local and web types).
4. Local CLI provider — wire first local agent (claude CLI as reference implementation).
5. Web provider — WKWebView panel for Gemini or similar with cookie and session persistence.
6. Unified chat UX — single input surface routing to the active provider.
7. Additional providers — copilot, codex, gemini-cli, and more web URLs.

## Local Configuration
- Preserve project-local SwarmForge configuration under swarmforge/.
- Keep swarm state local under .swarmforge/, worktrees under .worktrees/, and shared scripts under swarmforge/scripts/.

## Handoffs
- Prefer terse, explicit handoffs that report state and request role-appropriate review. Do not include verifications or sender process narrative.

## Ownership
- Do not change another role's prompt or workflow ownership without explicit user direction.
